RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHOTSHELL lead the way into the first turn and into the second turn, was in a long drive entering the home stretch was kept to task to prevail wire to wire. BOUGIE JOE rushed along the inside into the first turn to stalk the pace down the backstretch, inched closer to the leader throughout the far turn, dug in gamely in the early stretch but was no match in the end. GOLDEN FLASH chased the pace from the inside down the backstretch, gained the third position heading into the far turn and held on throughout and was always best for the show prize in the end. RANSAM PAYNTER raced in the middle of the pack while two wide, bid on the far turn then flattened out in the stretch and was no threat. KENTUCKY ICE stalked the pace while two wide, then faded heading into the second turn and had no final bid in the end. DR VINNIE BOOMBATZ settle along the inside throughout and showed little. NORBERT settled in the two path close behind the field and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 13500. (PLUS UP TO $675 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEET TAPIN MORO pressed the pace from two wide, overtook the pacesetter in mid-stretch and held off the closer in a drive to the line. WITT AMERICA stalked the pace from the fence through the turn, cut the corner turning for home and closed well from the inside to just miss. SMARTY RIDGE slow early to be at the back of the field, swung out turning for home and rallied belatedly in the stretch. MALORIE'S BIG BOY took the lead shortly from the gate, set a well measured pace while in hand and lacked a response when called upon at the top of the lane. TEXAS HOLDEM tracked the leaders from the rail, was set to an early drive and flattened out. FANDO chased the pace from two wide in the turn and faded down the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERFECT WISH moved up throughout the first turn to press the pace down the backstretch, then gained command at the top of the far turn and held sway down the home stretch to succeed in the end. SUNNY SAN LEON was well rated while tracking the pace from the inside throughout the first three quarters, then closed belatedly in the stretch to be up for the place prize. ALMOST DIALED OUT lead the way into the first turn to set the pace down the backstretch, then was headed at the top of the far bend by an outer rival, continued to bid gamely in the stretch and was out finished for the place prize. LUCKY DEPUTY chased the pace while two wide, was urging on the far turn to rally in the early stretch then continued to close well in the end. SCARLETTA stalked the pace from the two path down the backstretch, made a mild bid on the far turn then weakened in the stretch. SWEET SLEW trailed behind the field and was no factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 1 1/8M Turf CR: 94. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $3,000 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 18, 2021 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since April 18, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Eighth.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATHOLIC GUILT unhurried for the first three-quarters, angled out five wide turning for home and closed with a rush to be up in time in a determined effort. DEVAMANI (FR) well placed down the backside saving ground along the fence, cut the corner at the top of the lane, rallied along the inside to lead briefly in deep stretch but was caught late by the charging winner. EASTER SNAP taken in hand in the first turn to settle into a stalking position down the backstretch, rallied midway on the final bend to loom boldly at the head of the lane and was out-finished late in the drive. MAGIC MOSCO sped to the lead down the lane the first time, set a pressured pace throughout, drifted out in the final bend and weakened inside the final sixteenth. MIDAS CAT slow early to trail the field, commenced a long drive in the final turn and made up ground in the stretch. DARE TO BE WILD circled three wide in the first turn to challenge the leader down the backstretch and came up empty after three-quarters. BLING'S BELLWETHER showed brief speed and was through early.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROUGHNECK sped to a clear lead shortly from the gate while in hand, opened his advantage in the turn without being asked, came under mild urging in mid-stretch when kept to task and was geared down nearing the wire as much the best. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LET FREEDOM BLING set the pace along the inside, then vied briefly to keep the lead on the turn, kicked clear in the upper stretch and held on well proving best in the end. MIDSUMMER SOIREE was well rated while four wide throughout the first furlongs, was urging on the turn then found the best stride late stretch and just missed in the end. THINKITASADONATION moved up while three wide to vie for the lead between rivals heading into the turn. was in a steady drive then gave way in the end. FLY CONDOR chased the pace while two wide into the turn at an even effort, then closed well in the stretch. QUEEN GLADYS raced behind the field, then bid from the four path on the turn to rally from the sixth path in the stretch but it was too little too late. SADIE'S RANSOM chased the pace from the inside and remained in close throughout the turn and into the early stretch then gave way in the end. GETONOUTTAHERE raced in the back of the pack while two wide, then bid on the turn and was no threat. ZINASDESTINYVIRAGO move up while four wide to vie for the lead with two inner rivals heading into the turn, was in a hard drive throughout then weakened in the late stretch.

Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VIVACIOUSLY dueled throughout the first three quarters with an outer rival, then drew off in the stretch and was kept to task to win easily in the end. MISS LONG LEGS chased the pace under a steady drive while four wide down the backstretch and into the far turn, and was closing well but it wasn't enough. OCCURRENCE chased the pace while three wide, was in a hard drive throughout the far turn then closed well for the show prize. HAUNTED DREAM veered out and bumped rival at the start, then was unhurried early, rallied from the three path on the far turn but came up evenly in the stretch. NUBILITY was bumped on both sides at the start, then settled in the back of the pack, bid from the two path on the far turn, was in tight then steadied, angled out four wide in the stretch to rebid but came up empty. A LITTLE GOOD NEWS chased the pace from the inside, made a mild bid on the far turn then flattened out in the stretch. NICAMINE was bumped at the start, then settled along the inside throughout and showed little. GILDED GHOST chased the pace while three wide down the backstretch, then dropped back at the top of the far turn and had no final bid. SAN MATEO KAT dueled for the lead while two wide, was in a long drive heading into the second turn then weakened in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 10 5F Turf CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts). (If Deemed inadvisable by manageme nt to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: D'ORO STREET sped up the fence to take control shortly from the gate, set a well measured pace while under constant pressure, shook clear at the head of the lane, opened a clear advantage in mid-stretch and held in convincing fashion not having been threatened in the lane. LOANA tracked the pace in the clear several lengths back, dropped to the rail into the turn, saved all the ground cutting the corner and rallied well in the stretch for the place. ACCELERATE JUDY initially pressed the early pace from between horses, took back to settle in a stalking position, made a three wide bid turning for home to threaten but finished evenly down the lane. HIGINIA unhurried to be at the back of the main body of the field and rallied belatedly down the stretch to be gaining ground late. MAGNOLIA MAE well placed along the rail to the turn and flattened out approaching the quarter pole. MASTER SOM moved up three wide after the first eighth to press the pacesetter from three wide, dueled with the winner through the turn and gave way down the lane. MY BUTTERFLY raced mid-pack through the turn and faded. SASSY CHASSIE trailed throughout as a non-factor.
